[Term]
id: CL:0020015
name: transitional principal-intercalated cell of kidney collecting duct
def: "A transitional cell located in the renal collecting duct that co-expresses markers of both principal cell (PC) and intercalated cell (IC). This hybrid cell is enriched in Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD)." [PMID:33893305, PMID:37468583]
