[Term]
id: CL:0020017
name: M0 macrophage
def: "A macrophage that has not yet undergone polarization into a specific macrophage subtype. These cells are non-activated and have the potential to differentiate into inflammatory (M1) or alternatively activated (M2) macrophage subtypes in response to appropriate stimuli." [DOI:10.1186/s12885-022-09872-y, PMID:30861466]
