[Term]
id: CL:4023036
name: pvalb chandelier GABAergic interneuron
def: "A transcriptomically distinct pvalb GABAergic interneuron located in the pallium. It is recognizable by the straight terminal axonal 'cartridges' of vertically oriented strings of synaptic boutons. Chandelier PV cells' boutons target exclusively the axon initial segment (AIS) of pyramidal cells, with a single cell innervating hundreds of pyramidal cells in a clustered manner.  These cells are fast-spiking." [PMID:15378039, PMID:27199673, PMID:27477017, PMID:37824655]
comment: The marker set GPR149, CA8 can identify the Human cell type pvalb chandelier GABAergic interneuron in the neocortex with a confidence of 0.799748111 (NS-Forest FBeta value). {xref="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.11165918"}
