[Term]
id: CL:4033019
name: ON-blue cone bipolar cell
def: "An ON bipolar cell type with dendrites selectively contacting S-cones." [PMID:32032773]
comment: The axons of a blue cone bipolar cell terminate close to the ganglion cell layer, where they transfer the S-cone ON signal to small bistratified ganglion cells. Other targets of a blue cone bipolar cell include amacrine cells and possibly large bistratified ganglion cells. The marker set SORCS3, TAFA1 can identify the Human cell type http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_4033019 in the retina with a confidence of 0.709302326 (NS-Forest FBeta value). The marker set TAFA1, ENSG00000250971 can identify the Human cell type http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CL_4033019 in the retina with a confidence of 0.797269292 (NS-Forest FBeta value). {xref="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.11165918", xref="PMID:32032773"}
