[Term]
id: CL:4047048
name: type 4 muscularis propria glia
def: "An enteric glial cell characterized by a small central soma that extends long, thin, bipolar projections. This cell is primarily located along small nerve fibers within the muscle layers of the gastrointestinal tract and is known for its unbranching processes that closely follow these nerve fibers in the muscularis." [PMID:33731961, PMID:34401661]
synonym: "intramuscular glia" RELATED [PMID:34401661]
